<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="586" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[2082,2669,2246,2672]" lastBlockId="15.[1466,2668,2678,3457]" pageId="15" pageNumber="586">
This taxon has often been called 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Bubalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="15" pageNumber="586" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aequinoctialis">aequinoctialis</taxonomicName>
, and the name 
<taxonomicName box="[2388,2525,2368,2397]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Bubalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="15" pageNumber="586" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachyceros">brachyceros</taxonomicName>
has been applied to what are likely hybrids between this species and the Forest Buffalo (S. 
<taxonomicName box="[2085,2169,2490,2515]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Syncerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="15" pageNumber="586" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nanus">nanus</taxonomicName>
), which occurs in southern parts of 
<collectingCountry box="[2128,2231,2525,2554]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="15" pageNumber="586">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[2256,2446,2525,2554]" name="Sierra Leone" pageId="15" pageNumber="586">Sierra Leone</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[2472,2573,2525,2554]" name="Liberia" pageId="15" pageNumber="586">Liberia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry name="Ivory Coast" pageId="15" pageNumber="586">Ivory Coast</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[2245,2340,2568,2593]" name="Ghana" pageId="15" pageNumber="586">Ghana</collectingCountry>
. Recent study of more abundant museum material shows that the buffalo originally found around Lake 
<collectingCountry box="[1467,1543,2678,2711]" name="Chad" pageId="15" pageNumber="586">Chad</collectingCountry>
, the type locality of 
<taxonomicName box="[1841,1979,2678,2711]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Bubalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="15" pageNumber="586" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachyceros">brachyceros</taxonomicName>
, represent a different species we are calling the Lake 
<collectingCountry box="[1544,1618,2726,2751]" name="Chad" pageId="15" pageNumber="586">Chad</collectingCountry>
Buffalo. Synonyms include 
<taxonomicName box="[2011,2184,2726,2751]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Bubalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="15" pageNumber="586" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aequinoctialis">aequinoctialis</taxonomicName>
, azrakensis, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hinton" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[2346,2450,2726,2751]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Oreotragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="15" pageNumber="586" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="centralis">centralis</taxonomicName>
, neumanni, and solvayi. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
